						<summary>

						<p>This inscription, which is in Sanskrit, is damaged and undated. It states that a certain Aṇṇāji who is described as a favourite of the (Vijayanagara) king <hi rend="bold">Achyuta</hi> made a grant of the village <hi rend="bold">Kallahaḷḷi</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Siṅgā-Bhaṭṭa,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Liṅgā-Bhaṭṭa</hi> of Bhāradvāja-<hi rend="italic">gōtra,</hi> Āpastamba-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and Yajuś-<hi rend="italic">śākhā.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
